## 2. The MAF Stack - Your Available Tools

### Agent Mail (MCP)
**What it is:** Asynchronous messaging system for agent coordination

**Key capabilities:**
- Send/receive messages between agents
- File reservations (prevent conflicts)
- Threaded conversations per task
- Searchable audit trail

**How to use:**
```bash
# Register your identity (first time only)
mcp-agent-mail register __PROJECT_NAME__ __YOUR_AGENT_NAME__

# Check for messages
mcp-agent-mail inbox

# Send message to another agent
mcp-agent-mail send __RECIPIENT__ "Subject: [TASK-ID] Your message"

# Reserve files before editing
mcp-agent-mail reserve __YOUR_AGENT_NAME__ "path/to/file/**"

# Release files when done
mcp-agent-mail release __YOUR_AGENT_NAME__ "path/to/file/**"
```

**When to use:**
- Before starting work (announce intent)
- When blocked (escalate issue)
- On completion (notify others)
- For file reservations (prevent conflicts)

### Beads (Dependency-Aware Task Planning)
**What it is:** Lightweight issue database with dependency tracking

**Key capabilities:**
- Task tracking with priorities
- Dependency management
- Status tracking (open, in-progress, closed)
- CLI for workflow automation

**How to use:**
```bash
# Find ready work (no blockers)
bd ready

# Claim a bead
bd assign __BEAD_ID__ __YOUR_AGENT_NAME__

# Mark in progress
bd update __BEAD_ID__ --status in-progress

# Complete a bead
bd close __BEAD_ID__ --reason "Completed with tests passing"

# Check what's blocking a bead
bd blockers __BEAD_ID__
```

**When to use:**
- Finding next task to work on
- Updating task status
- Checking dependencies
- Tracking completion

### Role Spawning (tmux)
**What it is:** Multi-agent session management

**Agent roles in this project:**
- **Supervisor:** __SUPERVISOR__ - Coordinates work, assigns tasks, resolves conflicts
- **Reviewer:** __REVIEWER__ - Code quality, spec compliance, final approval
- **Implementor 1:** __IMP1__ - Implementation work (fluid assignment)
- **Implementor 2:** __IMP2__ - Implementation work (fluid assignment)

**How to coordinate:**
1. Supervisor assigns beads via Agent Mail
2. Implementors claim beads and announce work
3. Reviewer validates completion
4. All coordination via Agent Mail threads

